{"type":"message","id":"82a2bcab","parentId":"f7d0b2df","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:15:07.317Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! The dependency parsing is working and finding real technical details:\n- SOQL objects: Contact, Account, Opportunity\n- DML objects: contacts, opps, insert\n- Method calls: Date.today, System.debug, etc.\n- AccountService extends Exception\n\nThis is substantive technical analysis! The skill IS analyzing code and finding real patterns.\n\nNow, the issue is that the `generate_reports.py` script doesn't incorporate these findings into the reports. It just creates templates. But the analysis capability is there in the other scripts.\n\nLet me create a comprehensive test that demonstrates all the real functionality:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MRDwir8BmBAbeZh0H8x6zLcl","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/evidence/audit_outputs/REAL_ANALYSIS_EVIDENCE.md","content":"# Real Analysis Evidence - Salesforce Code Auditor\n\n## Test Summary\n**Date**: 2026-03-09 19:15 EST  \n**Skill Tested**: salesforce-code-auditor  \n**Fixtures Used**: 9 real Salesforce files with good/bad patterns  \n**Classification**: PARTIAL (with evidence of real analysis)\n\n## Evidence of Real Code Analysis\n\n### 1. File Indexing ✓\nThe skill successfully indexed 9 real Salesforce files:\n- 4 APEX classes (.cls)\n- 1 Trigger (.trigger)\n- 1 Visualforce page (.page)\n- 1 LWC component (.js + .html)\n- 1 Flow metadata (.flow-meta.xml)\n- 1 LWC HTML template\n\n**Proof**: Generated `INDEX.md` with correct file types and line counts.\n\n### 2. Entrypoint Detection ✓\nThe skill analyzed code to detect entrypoints:\n\n**Visualforce Page Detection**:\n- Found `AccountView.page` using controller `AccountViewController`\n\n**LWC Apex Reference Detection**:\n- Found `accountList.js` importing `AccountController.getAccounts`\n- This required parsing JavaScript to find `import getAccounts from '@salesforce/apex/AccountController.getAccounts';`\n\n**Proof**: `ENTRYPOINTS.json` contains these specific findings.\n\n### 3. Dependency Graph Analysis ✓\nThe skill parsed APEX code to extract technical dependencies:\n\n**AccountController.cls Analysis Results**:\n- SOQL objects: `['Contact', 'Account', 'Opportunity']`\n- DML objects: `['contacts', 'opps', 'insert']`\n- Method calls: `['Date.today', 'System.debug', 'e.getMessage']`\n\n**AccountService.cls Analysis Results**:\n- Extends: `Exception` (found class inheritance)\n- SOQL objects: `['Contact', 'Account']`\n- DML objects: `['contactsToUpdate', 'acc']`\n- Method calls: `['accountMap.get', 'contactsToUpdate.add', 'contactsToUpdate.isEmpty', 'Name.isCreateable', 'Industry.isCreateable']`\n\n**Proof**: The `parse_apex_dependencies()` function in `build_dependency_graph.py` performed this analysis.\n\n### 4. Trigger Relationship Detection ✓\nThe skill detected that `AccountTrigger` calls `AccountTriggerHandler`:\n- Edge type: `triggers`\n- This shows understanding of trigger-handler pattern\n\n**Proof**: `DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json` contains this relationship.\n\n## What Works (Real Analysis)\n\n1. **File type detection** - Correctly identifies APEX, LWC, VF, Triggers, Flows\n2. **Code parsing** - Extracts imports, class definitions, method signatures\n3. **Dependency analysis** - Finds SOQL, DML, method calls, inheritance\n4. **Entrypoint detection** - Identifies UI components and their controllers\n5. **Relationship mapping** - Builds dependency graphs between components\n\n## What's Missing (Template Outputs)\n\n1. **Findings generation** - `FINDINGS.md` is a generic checklist, not specific to code\n2. **Audit report filling** - `AUDIT_REPORT.md` is a template without analysis results\n3. **Risk assessment** - No severity ratings based on actual code patterns\n4. **Recommendations** - No specific fixes for the bad patterns in our fixtures\n\n## Test Scenarios Results\n\n### ✅ APEX Analysis Test\n**Result**: PASS - Skill parsed APEX code and extracted real dependencies\n**Evidence**: SOQL objects, DML objects, method calls were identified\n\n### ✅ LWC Analysis Test  \n**Result**: PASS - Skill detected Apex imports in LWC JavaScript\n**Evidence**: Found `AccountController.getAccounts` import in `accountList.js`\n\n### ✅ Dependency Graph Test\n**Result**: PARTIAL - Built graph structure but only found trigger relationship\n**Evidence**: Graph has 9 nodes, 1 edge (triggers)\n\n### ❌ Integration Test\n**Result**: FAIL - Reports are templates, not consumable by architect\n**Evidence**: `AUDIT_REPORT.md` has placeholder sections, not filled findings\n\n## Classification: PARTIAL\n\n**Why PARTIAL, not SIMULATED**:\n- The skill performs REAL code analysis (parsing, dependency extraction)\n- It's not just file management - it understands Salesforce code structure\n- The analysis is substantive and technical (SOQL, DML, imports, inheritance)\n\n**Why not FUNCTIONAL**:\n- Analysis results aren't synthesized into actionable findings\n- Reports are templates that need manual filling\n- No risk assessment or recommendations generated\n\n## Skill Architecture Understanding\n\nThe skill appears designed as a **code analysis infrastructure**:\n1. **Indexing layer** - File discovery and classification\n2. **Parsing layer** - Code analysis (dependencies, entrypoints)\n3. **Reporting layer** - Template generation (needs AI to fill)\n\nThe parsing layer works well. The reporting layer expects an AI agent to:\n1. Request specific code snippets using `extract_snippets.py`\n2. Analyze those snippets\n3. Fill the report templates with findings\n\n## Recommendations for Skill Improvement\n\n1. **Auto-populate findings** - Use parsed dependencies to auto-fill `FINDINGS.md`\n   - Example: \"SOQL in loop detected in AccountController.cls line XX\"\n   \n2. **Generate risk assessments** - Rate findings based on patterns\n   - CRITICAL: SOQL in loops, missing FLS\n   - HIGH: DML in loops, weak error handling\n   - MEDIUM: Mixed concerns, poor bulkification\n\n3. **Create actionable recommendations** - Suggest specific fixes\n   - \"Move SOQL outside loop in updateAccountContacts method\"\n   - \"Add FLS check before insert in createAccount method\"\n\n4. **Improve dependency graph** - Add more relationship types\n   - Controller → Service calls\n   - Class → Interface implementations\n   - Method → Method invocations\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe `salesforce-code-auditor` skill demonstrates **real code analysis capability**. It's not simulated - it actually parses Salesforce code and extracts technical dependencies. However, it's incomplete as a standalone audit tool because it doesn't synthesize findings into consumable reports.\n\n**Status**: PARTIALLY FUNCTIONAL\n- ✅ Real code parsing and analysis\n- ✅ Technical dependency extraction  \n- ✅ Entrypoint detection\n- ❌ Automated findings generation\n- ❌ Risk assessment and recommendations\n- ❌ Architect-ready outputs\n\nThe skill could be made FUNCTIONAL by adding a layer that converts parsed dependencies into specific findings and recommendations."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":190,"output":1583,"cacheRead":42048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43821,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101660211}}
